> Should the pie pan be greased/buttered?
**assistant**:
> Yes, it's a good idea to grease or butter the pie pan before pressing the pecan crust into it. Greasing the pan ensures that the crust doesn't stick to the pan and allows for easy removal of the tart once it's baked. You can use butter, cooking spray, or a light coating of vegetable oil to grease the pan. This will help in achieving a crisp and clean crust for your apple-pear tart.
